explains: adj. 不确定的，非决定性的，无结果的

sentences.en: The scientist has frowned, looked at the graphs, and said "the data are still inconclusive."
sentences.cn: 这位科学家皱了皱眉头，看了看图表，然后说：“数据仍然不确定。”

sentences.en: Research has so far proved inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 迄今为止研究还没有任何定论。

sentences.en: The past two elections were inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 过去的两次选举都没有结果。
